1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,600
Ever wonder why we only hear what we want?

2
00:00:03,600 --> 00:00:04,800
Meet myside bias.

3
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:09,600
It's when we favor our side's arguments, ignoring anything that contradicts them.

4
00:00:09,600 --> 00:00:10,400
But wait!

5
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:11,200
There's more.

6
00:00:11,200 --> 00:00:13,600
Confirmation bias is the sneaky cousin.

7
00:00:13,600 --> 00:00:18,000
It drives us to seek out evidence that confirms our beliefs.

8
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:19,200
Both are traps.

9
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:25,200
Research suggests these biases can distort our reality, affecting decisions from politics to personal relationships.

10
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:26,400
Awareness is key.

11
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:29,200
Recognizing these traps helps us think clearer.

12
00:00:29,200 --> 00:00:31,200
Curious about your own biases?

13
00:00:31,200 --> 00:00:33,200
Start questioning your beliefs today!

14
00:00:33,200 --> 00:00:35,600
Like and follow for more insights.
